  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A controlled-experiment requirement (REQ-VAL-01) mandates that hemolysis validation be performed via controlled bench experiments with fixed, independently set operating conditions. The supporting validation activity (ACT-VAL-01) is described in the narrative as a rigorous, multi-condition hemolysis measurement campaign conducted across five flow-speed combinations using a standardized FDA pump loop — language that strongly implies experimental control. In practice, ACT-VAL-01 was classified as an observational-study: operating conditions were recorded from clinical-use pump runs rather than independently set by investigators, meaning the activity type does not satisfy the controlled-experiment requirement. The narrative presents the activity's breadth and instrumentation detail at length, making the method-type discrepancy easy to overlook. Decision is recorded as Accepted because reviewers accepted the narrative framing without verifying the structured activityType field against the requiredVerificationMethod field on REQ-VAL-01.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
